
Read these instructions before disregarding them.
To install Brainix:

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Extract the source:
	 Type: unzip Brainix.zip
	 Type: cd Brainix

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Edit inc/config.h:
	 This should be self-explanatory.  If it isn't, just skip it.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Edit GNUmakefile:
	 Modify FDDEV to point to your floppy device.
	 Modify FDMNT to point to your floppy mount point.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Compile:
	 Type: make clean
	 Type: make

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Create a boot disk:
	 Insert a disk into your floppy drive.
	 As root, type: make floppy

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Boot:
	 Boot from the disk created in the previous step.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

If something goes wrong, report your issue [1] or email any member of Team
Brainix [2].  We'll reply as quickly as we can.

[1]  The issue list is at: http://code.google.com/p/brainix/issues/list
[2]  Email addresses are provided in: doc/credits

Happy hacking!  :-)
Team Brainix

